Key Match Events: Christian Kouamé scored the first goal for Ivory Coast in the 1st minute of the match.
Seko Fofana scored the second goal for Ivory Coast in the 2nd minute of the match.
Franck Kessié recorded his first tournament assist for Ivory Coast.
Karim Konaté and Simon Adingra received yellow cards for Ivory Coast.
Mohamed Badamosi received a yellow card for The Gambia.
Hamza Barry and Assan Ceesay received tactical substitutions for The Gambia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Benjamini Mkapa National Stadium.
The referee for the match was Jalal Jayed.
The starting line-ups and substitutes for both teams were listed.
Others: The match was part of the World Cup Qualification Africa Group F.
